vices such as GSS cadet leader training and Project Success  Referrals to the Miller Academic Center  Faculty and staff refer students to the Miller Academic Center  Class workshops  Miller Academic Center staff visit a number of classrooms each year to provide instructions to cadets on various study skills  Resources on learning strategies  Faculty and staff consult with the Miller Academic Center regarding academic resources and various learning strategies and vice versa to ensure accurate and consistent support for cadets  Collaborations on various grants and projects  Faculty and Miller Academic Center staff seek opportunities to collaborate on projects such as the development of a first year experience program  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Pro