rmation Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Preston Library Preston Library Library Home Library Home Find Books Find Books Departments Departments Media Equipment Media Equipment Technical Services Technical Services Visitor Information Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Archives Archives Archives Home Archives Home Online Exhibits Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Civil War   New Market Give Give Close Menu Academic Services   Support Miller Academic Center Help with Study Skills Project Success Group Study Sessions Faculty Involvement History of the Center Staff P   540  464 7661 F   540  464 7798 Miller Academic Center Virginia Military Institute 202 Carroll Hall Lexington  VA  24450 Contact Miller Academic Center Faculty Involvement The Miller Academic Center values involvement and cooperation with faculty and staff in an effort to better meet the needs of cadets  Please feel free to contact any member of the Miller Academic Center with questions or comments  Faculty Involvement Group Study Session  GSS  cadet leader selection  Faculty and staff provide cadet recommendations for GSS cadet leaders  Group Study Session  GSS faculty team members  Each GSS has a faculty member from the department for that course who serves as a resource both for the cadet leader s  as well as the Miller Academic Center to contribute to the overall effectiveness of the GSS experience  Professional development   The Miller Academic Center provides speakers and seminars for faculty and staff on a variety of topics  Enhancement of Miller Academic Center programs  Representatives of departments and programs serve as guest speakers to enhance MAC programs and services such as GSS cadet leader training and Project Success  Referrals to the Miller Academic Center  Faculty and staff refer students to the Miller Academic Center  Class workshops  Miller Academic Center staff visit a number of classrooms each year to provide instructions to cadets on various study skills  Resources on learning strategies  Faculty and staff consult with the Miller Academic Center regarding academic resources and various learning strategies and vice versa to ensure accurate and consistent support for cadets  Collaborations on various grants and projects  Faculty and Miller Academic Center staff seek opportunities to collaborate on projects such as the development of a first year experience program Academic Services   Support Miller Academic Center Help with Study Skills Project Success Group Study Sessions Faculty Involvement History of the Center Staff P   540  464 7661 F   540  464 7798 Miller Academic Center Virginia Military Institute 202 Carroll Hall Lexington  VA  24450 Contact Miller Academic Center  Academic Services   Support Miller Academic Center Help with Study Skills Project Success Group Study Sessions Faculty Involvement History of the Center Staff P   540  464 7661 F   540  464 7798 Miller Academic Center Virginia Military Institute 202 Carroll Hall Lexington  VA  24450 Contact Miller Academic Center Academic Services   Support Miller Academic Center Help with Study Skills Project Success Group Study Sessions Faculty Involvement History of the Center Staff Academic Services   Support Academic Services   Support Miller Academic Center Miller Academic Center Help with Study Skills Help with Study Skills Project Success Project Success Group Study Sessions Group Study Sessions 