iller Academic Center staff seek opportunities to collaborate on projects such as the development of a first year experience program      Faculty Involvement The Miller Academic Center values involvement and cooperation with faculty and staff in an effort to better meet the needs of cadets  Please feel free to contact any member of the Miller Academic Center with questions or comments  Faculty Involvement Group Study Session  GSS  cadet leader selection  Faculty and staff provide cadet recommendations for GSS cadet leaders  Group Study Session  GSS faculty team members  Each GSS has a faculty member from the department for that course who serves as a resource both for the cadet leader s  as well as the Miller Academic Center to contribute to the overall effectiveness of the GSS experience  Professional development   The Miller Academic Center provides speakers and seminars for faculty and staff on a variety of topics  Enhancement of Miller Academic Center programs  Representatives of departments and programs serve as guest speakers to enhance MAC programs and services such as GSS cadet leader training and Project Success  Referrals to the Miller Academic Center  Faculty and staff refer students to the Miller Academic Center  Class workshops  Miller Academic Center staff visit a number of classrooms each year to provide instructions to cadets on various study skills  Resources on learning strategies  Faculty and staff consult with the Miller Academic Center regarding academic resources and various learning strategies and vice versa to ensure accurate and consistent support for cadets  Collaborations on various grants and projects  Faculty and Miller Academic Center staff seek opportunities to collaborate on projects such as the development of a first year experience program Faculty Involvement The Miller Academic Center values involvement and cooperation with faculty and staff in an effort to better meet the needs of cadets  Please feel free to contact any member of 